BEFORE THE STATE CONSUMER DISPUTES REDRESSAL COMMISSION
{PLACE}

Appeal No. _____ of 20__
(Appeal under Section 41 read with Section 24(5) of the Consumer Protection Act, 2019)

IN THE MATTER OF:
{USER_NAME}, {ADDRESS}
... Appellant
— versus —
1. {BENEFICIARY_BANK} (through its Branch Manager & Nodal Officer)
2. {BANK_NAME} (issuing bank of VPA {VPA})
... Respondents

Memo of Appeal against the Order of the District Commission dated {OMBUDSMAN_ORDER_DATE} (ref {OMBUDSMAN_REF})

Sir/Madam,

1. The Appellant, {USER_NAME} (VPA {VPA}; mobile {MOBILE_NO}; email {EMAIL}), aggrieved by the order of the District Consumer Disputes Redressal Commission, {PLACE}, dated {OMBUDSMAN_ORDER_DATE} (ref {OMBUDSMAN_REF}), files this appeal under Section 41 of the Consumer Protection Act, 2019 within the limitation period prescribed under Section 24(5).

2. Background:
   (i) On {TXN_DATE}, the Appellant made a wrong UPI transfer of Rs. {AMOUNT} (UTR {UTR}) from VPA {VPA} to VPA {VPA_PAYEE}, credited to account {BENEFICIARY_ACCOUNT_NO} (IFSC {BENEFICIARY_IFSC}) at Respondent No. 1 ({BENEFICIARY_BANK});
   (ii) DRM complaint dated {COMPLAINT_DATE} (ticket {TICKET_NO}) failed after {DAYS_ELAPSED} days;
   (iii) District Commission complaint was filed but dismissed / partially allowed vide order dated {OMBUDSMAN_ORDER_DATE}.

3. Grounds of Appeal:
   (a) The District Commission erred in not directing Respondent No. 1 to effect the reversal despite its admitted failure to comply with NPCI DRM (per DPSS.CO.PD.No.629/02.06.005/2019-20, Section 4);
   (b) The Commission failed to award adequate compensation of Rs. {COMPENSATION_DUE} for {HOURS_LOST} hours lost at Rs. {HOUR_RATE}/hour (totalling Rs. {TIME_COST_AMOUNT});
   (c) The Commission did not take into account the Respondent's breach of Consumer Protection Act 2019, Section 2(11) (deficiency in service) and Section 2(7) (consumer);
   (d) The out-of-pocket expenses of Rs. {OUT_OF_POCKET} were not reimbursed.

4. Relief sought on appeal:
   (a) Set aside / modify the District Commission's order dated {OMBUDSMAN_ORDER_DATE};
   (b) Direct Respondent No. 1 to refund Rs. {AMOUNT} with interest at 12% p.a. from {TXN_DATE};
   (c) Award compensation of Rs. {COMPENSATION_DUE} for mental agony and deficiency in service;
   (d) Direct Respondent No. 1 to bear the costs of litigation including Rs. {OUT_OF_POCKET}.

Place: {PLACE}
Date: {TODAY_DATE}

Appellant:
{USER_NAME}
Mobile: {MOBILE_NO}
Email: {EMAIL}

